definition.value: A cyclic hydroxamic acid that is 1-hydroxypyridin-2(1H)-one in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6 are substituted by methyl and benzyl groups, respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of mutant isocitrate dehydrogenase 1 (Ki values of 190 nM against R132H mutant and 120 nM against R132C mutant).
6-(4-hydroxybenzyl)-4-methyl-1-hydroxypyridin-2(1H)-one
6-Benzyl-1-hydroxypyridin-2(1H)-one
6-Benzyl-4-isopropyl-1-hydroxypyridin-2(1H)-one
6-Phenyl-4-methyl-1-hydroxypyridin-2(1H)-one
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid carrying one or more hydroperoxy substituents.

A branched amino heptasaccharide derivative that is alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the beta-D-GlcNAc residue carries an alpha-L-Fuc residue via a (1->3) linkage and the the D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end carries two alpha-L-Fuc residues via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide that is beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue distal to the reducing end carries an alpha-L-fucosyl residue via a (1->3) linkage.
Any fatty acid containing two carboxy groups.

A branched amino hexasaccharide derivative that is alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the two GlcNAc residues each carry an alpha-L-Fuc residue via a (1->3) linkage.

A branched amino hexasaccharide derivative that is alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the beta-GlcNAc residue distal to the reducing end carries an alpha-L-Fuc residue via a (1->3) linkage and the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end carries an alpha-L-Fuc residue via a (1->6) linkage.

A branched amino heptasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the beta-GlcNAc residue distal to the reducing end carries an alpha-L-Fuc residue via a (1->3) linkage and the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end carries an alpha-L-Fuc residue via a (1->6) linkage.
Any fatty acid that contains 2 carboxylic groups. Major microspecies at pH 7.3
A lipid derived from phthiocerol.
An N(6)-acyl-L-lysine residue derived from N(6)-(9Z)-hexadec-9-enoyl]-L-lysine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from any N(6)-(fatty acyl)-L-lysine.
DOI: 10.1021/acscatal.1c04321
An alkyldiacylglyceride that has a 51 carbons and 2 double bonds in the alkyl and acyl chains (positions not specified).
A nitrile that is 3-phenylpropionitrile in which one of the methylene hydrogens at position 3 is replaced by a hydroxy group.

A racemate comprising equimolar amount of (2R,3S)-C75 and its enantiomer, (2S,3R)-C75. It is a fatty-acid synthase (FAS) inhibitor and an activator of carnitine palmitoyl-transferase-1 that leads to weight loss and feeding inhibition in mice.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (2R,3S)- and (2S,3R)-PPDA. It is a subtype-selective NMDA receptor antagonist that preferentially binds to GluN2C/GluN2D (formally NR2C/NR2D) containing receptors.

A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-[(4-ethylpiperazin-1-yl)methyl]-3-(trifluoromethyl)benzoic acid with the amino group of 5-(5-amino-2-methylphenoxy)-1,3-dihydro-2H-indol-2-one. It is a potent inhibitor of discoidin domain receptor tyrosine kinase 1 and 2 (DDR1/2) with IC50 = 105 nM and 413 nM, respectively.
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of Met-enkephalin. Major species at pH 7.3.
A peptide cation obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy terminus and protonation of the side-chain guanidino group and the amino terminus of Arg-Phe; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-(phenanthren-2-ylcarbonyl)piperazine-2,3-dicarboxylic acid that has 2R,3S-configuration.
A 1-(phenanthren-2-ylcarbonyl)piperazine-2,3-dicarboxylic acid that has 2S,3R-configuration.
A tertiary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of phenanthrene-2-carboxylic acid with the amino group of piperazine-2,3-dicarboxylic acid.
